211
00:17:58,720 --> 00:18:00,440
Mr. Xu, you have sharp eyes.

212
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,359
I almost wronged you just now.

213
00:18:02,359 --> 00:18:03,200
Sorry about that.

214
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,160
Let's move on to the second point.

215
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:13,359
The second direction is character-wise.

216
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,240
Even though these two books

217
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,680
share many similar plot devices,

218
00:18:16,799 --> 00:18:18,160
the male lead's character

219
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,319
is actually very different.

220
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,759
In my novel, the male lead...

221
00:18:27,319 --> 00:18:30,119
In my novel, the male lead

222
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,359
is quiet and elegant,

223
00:18:34,039 --> 00:18:35,119
